			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<strong>Company Overview:</strong></p>
<p>
	Interconnected healthcare systems continuously create challenges that provide market opportunity for the companies and individuals willing to think outside of the box.</p>
<p>
	At iNTERFACEWARE, we embrace these challenges and through our industry leading <a href="http://www.interfaceware.com/iguana.html">integration engine</a>, Iguana and our unwavering dedication to professional services, customer relationships and product support we continue to see growth and are expanding our operations.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	<strong>Job Description:</strong></p>
<p>
	iNTERFACEWARE, an innovation-driven healthcare integration market leader, is seeking a stellar sales manager to join our dynamic and growing sales team.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	This is a key role within our organization that will afford a talented and ambitious individual to have immediate and highly visible impact on the overall growth of the company.</p>
<p>
	In the long-term, with over 600 existing customers and a high-value differentiated product offering, iNTERFACEWARE is on a rapid revenue growth path that offers an unparalleled opportunity for continued sales success at the individual and team level.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<br />
	<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Convert and qualify inbound leads generated by marketing and communications programs.</li>
	<li>
		Identify key strategic opportunities and build long-term account plans, including prospecting, business development and team negotiation planning.</li>
	<li>
		Plan, document and execute complete end-to-end opportunity lifecycle, from qualification to contract negotiation and closing.</li>
	<li>
		Manage roster of key strategic accounts assigned, identify incremental opportunities and secure long-term revenue growth for the roster of key accounts.</li>
	<li>
		Accountable for personal revenue forecast tracking and delivery to assigned quarterly revenue goal.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		General understanding of software business and sales process.</li>
	<li>
		Analytical skills and awareness of the consultative selling methods.</li>
	<li>
		Written and verbal communication competency</li>
	<li>
		Working knowledge of office software packages</li>
	<li>
		Presentation development and delivery experience</li>
	<li>
		Valid passport/visa for business related travel to US, Canada and EU.</li>
	<li>
		Valid drivers license, recognized in US, Canada and EU</li>
</ul>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<strong>Work Conditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Office-based role, located at iNTERFACEWARE headquarters at 672 Dupont Street in Toronto, Ontario.</li>
	<li>
		Up to 50% travel</li>
</ul>
